<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1398,1047,1114]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">
General description: See 
<bibRefCitation author="Ricardo" box="[446,628,1048,1074]" firstAuthor="Ricardo" pageId="5" pageNumber="18" refString="Ricardo, G. (1925) New species of Asilidae from South Africa. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Zoology, Botany and Geology, (9) 15, 234 - 282." type="journal article" year="1925">Ricardo (1925)</bibRefCitation>
. Entire topotypic Ψ (
<figureCitation box="[871,977,1048,1074]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,269,902,926]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,341,888]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[761,1418,379,886]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic female habitus. 1. Dorsal. 2. Lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177464/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
), right wing of topotypic ♂ (
<figureCitation box="[1311,1382,1048,1074]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1561,1585]" captionTargetBox="[175,1391,1082,1525]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[175,1417,1050,1552]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic male wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177465/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Description ♂
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177467/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" targetBox="[350,1196,1109,1904]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1947,2005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,331,1947,1971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">FIGURES 9–12</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricardo, 1925" authorityName="Ricardo" authorityYear="1925" box="[347,755,1948,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Perasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transvaalensis">
<emphasis box="[347,590,1948,1971]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="14">Perasis transvaalensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ricardo, G." box="[599,755,1948,1971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" pagination="234 - 282" refId="ref5826" refString="Ricardo, G. (1925) New species of Asilidae from South Africa. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Zoology, Botany and Geology, (9) 15, 234 - 282." type="journal article" year="1925">Ricardo, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Topotypic male terminalia. 9. Lateral. 10. Dorsal. 11. Ventral view of hypandrium. 12. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,152,738]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">
Genital capsule of dissected male rotated counter-clockwise through about 90° (Note: this character is variable. Of 
<specimenCount box="[299,354,192,218]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" type="generic">15 ♂</specimenCount>
examined 8, were rotated counter-clockwise, 7 clockwise, and the degree of rotation varied between approx. 45–90°). Epandrium in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[796,883,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[350,1196,1109,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[350,1242,1109,1933]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic male terminalia. 9. Lateral. 10. Dorsal. 11. Ventral view of hypandrium. 12. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177467/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) obviously longer than wide (length: breadth ration = 1: 1.38), in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[549,619,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[350,1196,1109,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[350,1242,1109,1933]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic male terminalia. 9. Lateral. 10. Dorsal. 11. Ventral view of hypandrium. 12. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177467/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) broad, slightly curved, proximally slightly constricted ventrally, distally with broadly rounded end. Proctiger in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[825,910,312,338]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[350,1196,1109,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[350,1242,1109,1933]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic male terminalia. 9. Lateral. 10. Dorsal. 11. Ventral view of hypandrium. 12. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177467/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) narrowly rounded distally and projecting to same level attained by epandrial lobes. Hypandrium in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1000,1088,352,378]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[350,1196,1109,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[350,1242,1109,1933]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic male terminalia. 9. Lateral. 10. Dorsal. 11. Ventral view of hypandrium. 12. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177467/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) tapering sharply to narrow, somewhat truncated distal end. Gonocoxite in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[845,914,392,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[350,1196,1109,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[350,1242,1109,1933]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic male terminalia. 9. Lateral. 10. Dorsal. 11. Ventral view of hypandrium. 12. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177467/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with somewhat rounded appearance, dorsal lobe slender (usually visible in dry condition); gonostylus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1082,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–8" captionStartId="4.[151,270,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[238,1300,1065,1966]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[232,1337,1065,1992]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4–8. Perasis carpenteri Oldroyd, 1970. Holotype male terminalia. 4. Lateral. 5. Dorsal. 6. Ventral view of hypandrium. 7. Gonocoxite lateral view. 8. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177466/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) rounded apically and bearing an obviously backwardly-directed dorsal spine. Aedeagal base in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1116,1204,472,498]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[350,1196,1109,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[350,1242,1109,1933]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic male terminalia. 9. Lateral. 10. Dorsal. 11. Ventral view of hypandrium. 12. Ventral. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177467/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) with long distally directed lateral projections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,152,738]" box="[198,889,551,578]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">
Description of female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[577,715,552,578]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–14" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1414,1438]" captionTargetBox="[156,1408,794,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[156,1431,751,1421]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13–14. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic female terminalia. 13. Ventral. 14. Dorsal. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177468/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Figs 13–14</figureCitation>
: Topotypic Ψ):
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,152,738]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">
Terminalia dorsoventrally compressed. Hypogynium (
<figureCitation box="[846,934,592,618]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–14" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1414,1438]" captionTargetBox="[156,1408,794,1413]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[156,1431,751,1421]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 13–14. Perasis transvaalensis Ricardo, 1925. Topotypic female terminalia. 13. Ventral. 14. Dorsal. Scale line 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177468/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="15">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) with well-developed setose lateral lobes and a pair of smaller, somewhat truncate distomedial lobes bearing fine setulae. Proctiger with supraanale (cerci) fused basally, bilobed distally (
